  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO AMEND SECTION 21-1-59, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, TO DEFINE AN INDUSTRIAL ZONE AS A PROJECT WHOSE OPERATOR MAY ENTER INTO AN AGREEMENT WITH A MUNICIPALITY, FOR A PERIOD NOT TO EXCEED 30 YEARS, PROVIDING THAT THE MUNICIPALITY SHALL NOT ANNEX THE PROJECT SITE WITHOUT WRITTEN CONSENT FROM THE OPERATOR OF THE PROJECT; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
